{"id":952598138,"question_id":345,"lang":"java","lang_name":"Java","time":"1Â year","timestamp":1684399349,"status":10,"status_display":"Accepted","runtime":"5 ms","url":"/submissions/detail/952598138/","is_pending":"Not Pending","title":"Reverse Vowels of a String","memory":"42.6 MB","code":"class Solution {\n    public String reverseVowels(String s) {\n        HashSet<Character> set = new HashSet<>();\n        set.add('a');\n        set.add('e');\n        set.add('i');\n        set.add('o');\n        set.add('u');\n        set.add('A');\n        set.add('E');\n        set.add('I');\n        set.add('O');\n        set.add('U');\n        \n        \n        int len = s.length();\n        \n        int st =0, ed=len-1;\n        \n        char[] arr  = s.toCharArray();\n        \n        while(st<ed){\n            \n            while(st<len && !set.contains(s.charAt(st)))\n                st++;\n            \n            while(ed>0 && !set.contains(s.charAt(ed)))\n                ed--;\n            \n            \n            if(st<ed){\n                \n                char tmp = arr[st];\n                arr[st] = arr[ed];\n                arr[ed] = tmp;\n                st++;\n                ed--;\n            }\n        }\n        \n        return new String(arr);\n            \n                \n            \n    }\n}","compare_result":"","title_slug":"reverse-vowels-of-a-string","has_notes":false,"flag_type":1}
